# Database & Prisma Conventions

- Postgres runs via `docker compose up -d` (host port **5433**). `DATABASE_URL`,
  seed admin creds, and NextAuth vars live in `.env` (template: `.env.example`).
- Import the singleton client from `@/lib/prisma`. Never `new PrismaClient()` in
  app/API code (seed script is the only exception).

## Schema
- Extend existing models; keep enums (`ProductBadge`, `PaymentMethod`,
  `PaymentStatus`, `OrderStatus`, `Role`, `InventoryType`) authoritative.
- Preserve the unique constraints: `Product.slug`,
  `ProductVariant(productId, size, color)`, `CartItem(cartId, variantId)`,
  `WishlistItem(userId, productId)`.
- After editing `schema.prisma`: `npx prisma format && npx prisma validate`.

## Migrations
- Prefer `npx prisma migrate dev --name <change>` when the DB is reachable.
- If the daemon is down, hand-write the SQL under
  `prisma/migrations/<timestamp>_<name>/migration.sql` and make it data-safe
  (add nullable column → backfill → set NOT NULL), then apply later with
  `npx prisma migrate deploy`. Never edit an already-applied migration.

## Inventory invariant
- Any stock change MUST write an `InventoryTransaction` (IN / OUT / ADJUSTMENT)
  in the same `prisma.$transaction` that mutates `ProductVariant.stock`.
- Checkout decrements stock + logs OUT atomically; cancellations reverse it.
